"White Walls" is a song by an American hip hop duo composed of rapper Macklemore and record producer Ryan Lewis, from their collaborative debut studio album The Heist (2012). The song's hook is performed by singer-songwriter Hollis, while American rapper Schoolboy Q performs a guest verse."White Walls" is set to be released to American contemporary hit radio on October 8, 2013 as the sixth single from The Heist.The music video, directed by Macklemore, Ryan Lewis and Jason Koenig, was released September 9, 2013. The video features cameo appearances from several artists including A$AP Rocky, Trinidad Jame$, Wiz Khalifa, DJ Drama, Big Boi and Sir Mix-a-Lot.
